2399:
2400:## SpatialGrid
2401:
2402:A sparse occupied-cell grid that tracks which entities are at each cell. The World automatically syncs entity positions to the grid. You should **read** from the grid but not write to it directly.
2403:
2404:```typescript
2405:import { SpatialGrid, ORTHOGONAL, DIAGONAL, ALL_DIRECTIONS } from 'civ-engine';
2406:```
2407:
2408:### Properties
2409:
2410:| Property | Type | Description |
2411:|---|---|---|
2412:| `width` | `number` | Grid width (read-only) |
2413:| `height` | `number` | Grid height (read-only) |
2414:
2415:### Methods
2416:
2417:#### `getAt(x, y)`
2418:
2419:```typescript
2420:getAt(x: number, y: number): ReadonlySet<EntityId> | null
2421:```
2422:
2423:Returns the set of entities at a cell, or `null` if no entity is there. The returned set is read-only.
2424:
2425:**Throws:** `RangeError` if `(x, y)` is out of bounds.
2426:
2427:```typescript
2428:const entities = world.grid.getAt(5, 3);
2429:if (entities) {
2430:  for (const id of entities) {
2431:    console.log(`Entity ${id} is at (5, 3)`);
2432:  }
2433:}
2434:```
2435:
2436:#### `getNeighbors(x, y, offsets?)`
2437:
2438:```typescript
2439:getNeighbors(x: number, y: number, offsets?: ReadonlyArray<[number, number]>): EntityId[]
2440:```
2441:
2442:Returns all entities in neighboring cells. Automatically skips out-of-bounds cells.
2443:
2444:**Throws:** `RangeError` if `(x, y)` is out of bounds.
2445:
2446:| Parameter | Default | Description |
2447:|---|---|---|
2448:| `offsets` | `ORTHOGONAL` | Direction offsets to check |
2449:
2450:```typescript
2451:// 4 orthogonal neighbors (default)
2452:const nearby = world.grid.getNeighbors(5, 3);
2453:
2454:// 8 directions (orthogonal + diagonal)
2455:const allNearby = world.grid.getNeighbors(5, 3, ALL_DIRECTIONS);
2456:
2457:// Only diagonal
2458:const diag = world.grid.getNeighbors(5, 3, DIAGONAL);
2459:```
2460:
2461:### Direction Constants
2462:
2463:| Constant | Directions | Count |
2464:|---|---|---|
2465:| `ORTHOGONAL` | Up, Down, Left, Right | 4 |
2466:| `DIAGONAL` | Up-Left, Up-Right, Down-Left, Down-Right | 4 |
2467:| `ALL_DIRECTIONS` | All 8 | 8 |
2468:
2469:Each constant is `ReadonlyArray<[number, number]>` of `[dx, dy]` offsets.
2470:
2471:---
2472:
2473:## Pathfinding
2474:
2475:Generic A* pathfinding on any graph topology. Standalone utility with no dependency on World or SpatialGrid.
2476:
2477:```typescript
2478:import { findPath, type PathConfig, type PathResult } from 'civ-engine';
2479:```
2480:
2481:### `findPath<T>(config)`
2482:
2483:```typescript
2484:findPath<T>(config: PathConfig<T>): PathResult<T> | null
2485:```
2486:
2487:Finds the shortest path from `start` to `goal` using A*.
2488:
2489:**Returns:** `PathResult<T>` with the path and cost, or `null` if no path exists, the cost ceiling is exceeded, or the iteration limit is reached.
2490:
2491:**Behavior details:**
2492:- If `start === goal` (by hash), returns immediately with `{ path: [start], cost: 0 }`
2493:- Edges with `Infinity` cost are treated as impassable and skipped
2494:- Uses an internal min-heap for the open set
2495:- `maxCost` terminates early if the best known cost exceeds it
2496:- `maxIterations` prevents infinite loops on large graphs (default: 10,000)
2497:
2498:**Grid pathfinding example:**
2499:
2500:```typescript
2501:const WIDTH = 32;
2502:const HEIGHT = 32;
2503:
2504:const result = findPath<number>({
2505:  start: 0,         // top-left corner
2506:  goal: WIDTH * HEIGHT - 1,  // bottom-right corner
2507:  neighbors: (node) => {
2508:    const x = node % WIDTH;
2509:    const y = Math.floor(node / WIDTH);
2510:    const result: number[] = [];
2511:    if (x > 0) result.push(node - 1);
2512:    if (x < WIDTH - 1) result.push(node + 1);
2513:    if (y > 0) result.push(node - WIDTH);
2514:    if (y < HEIGHT - 1) result.push(node + WIDTH);
2515:    return result;
2516:  },
2517:  cost: () => 1,
2518:  heuristic: (node, goal) => {
2519:    return Math.abs((node % WIDTH) - (goal % WIDTH))
2520:         + Math.abs(Math.floor(node / WIDTH) - Math.floor(goal / WIDTH));
2521:  },
2522:  hash: (node) => node,
2523:  maxCost: 100,
2524:  trackExplored: true,
2525:});
2526:
2527:if (result) {
2528:  console.log(`Path: ${result.path.length} steps, cost: ${result.cost}`);
2529:  console.log(`Explored: ${result.explored} nodes`);
2530:}
2531:```
2532:
2533:**Graph pathfinding example (non-grid):**
2534:
2535:```typescript
2536:interface City { name: string; x: number; y: number }
2537:
2538:const cities: Record<string, City> = {
2539:  A: { name: 'A', x: 0, y: 0 },
2540:  B: { name: 'B', x: 3, y: 4 },
2541:  C: { name: 'C', x: 10, y: 0 },
2542:};
2543:
2544:const roads: Record<string, string[]> = {
2545:  A: ['B', 'C'],
2546:  B: ['A', 'C'],
2547:  C: ['A', 'B'],
2548:};
2549:
2550:const result = findPath<string>({
2551:  start: 'A',
2552:  goal: 'C',
2553:  neighbors: (city) => roads[city] ?? [],
2554:  cost: (from, to) => {
2555:    const a = cities[from];
2556:    const b = cities[to];
2557:    return Math.sqrt((a.x - b.x) ** 2 + (a.y - b.y) ** 2);
2558:  },
2559:  heuristic: (city, goal) => {
2560:    const a = cities[city];
2561:    const b = cities[goal];
2562:    return Math.sqrt((a.x - b.x) ** 2 + (a.y - b.y) ** 2);
2563:  },
2564:  hash: (city) => city,
2565:});
2566:```
2567:
