2570:## OccupancyGrid
2571:
2572:Deterministic blocked-cell, footprint, occupancy, and reservation tracking. Standalone utility that answers "can something stand here?" rather than "who is nearby?".
2573:
2574:```typescript
2575:import {
2576:  OccupancyGrid,
2577:  type OccupancyArea,
2578:  type OccupancyGridMetrics,
2579:  type OccupancyGridState,
2580:  type OccupancyQueryOptions,
2581:  type OccupancyRect,
2582:} from 'civ-engine';
2583:```
2584:
2585:### Constructor
2586:
2587:```typescript
2588:new OccupancyGrid(width: number, height: number)
2589:```
2590:
2591:Creates an empty occupancy model for a fixed grid size.
2592:
2593:| Parameter | Description |
2594:|---|---|
2595:| `width` | Positive integer grid width |
2596:| `height` | Positive integer grid height |
2597:
2598:### Properties
2599:
2600:| Property | Type | Description |
2601:|---|---|---|
2602:| `width` | `number` | Grid width (read-only) |
2603:| `height` | `number` | Grid height (read-only) |
2604:| `version` | `number` | Monotonic passability version incremented on mutations |
2605:
2606:### Methods
2607:
2608:#### `setBlocked(area, blocked)`
2609:
2610:```typescript
2611:setBlocked(area: OccupancyArea, blocked: boolean): void
2612:```
2613:
2614:Sets blocked status for a footprint or list of cells. Throws if a blocked write would overlap an occupied or reserved cell.
2615:
2616:#### `block(area)`
2617:
2618:```typescript
2619:block(area: OccupancyArea): void
2620:```
2621:
2622:Marks cells as blocked.
2623:
2624:#### `unblock(area)`
2625:
2626:```typescript
2627:unblock(area: OccupancyArea): void
2628:```
2629:
2630:Clears blocked cells.
2631:
2632:#### `isBlocked(x, y, options?)`
2633:
2634:```typescript
2635:isBlocked(x: number, y: number, options?: OccupancyQueryOptions): boolean
2636:```
2637:
2638:Returns `true` if the cell is blocked, occupied by another entity, or reserved by another entity.
2639:
2640:#### `canOccupy(entity, area, options?)`
2641:
2642:```typescript
2643:canOccupy(
2644:  entity: EntityId,
2645:  area: OccupancyArea,
2646:  options?: { includeReservations?: boolean },
2647:): boolean
2648:```
2649:
2650:Checks whether an entity may claim a footprint as occupied.
2651:
2652:#### `occupy(entity, area)`
2653:
2654:```typescript
2655:occupy(entity: EntityId, area: OccupancyArea): boolean
2656:```
2657:
2658:Claims a footprint for an entity. Returns `false` on conflict instead of throwing.
2659:
2660:#### `canReserve(entity, area)`
2661:
2662:```typescript
2663:canReserve(entity: EntityId, area: OccupancyArea): boolean
2664:```
2665:
2666:Checks whether an entity may reserve a footprint.
2667:
2668:#### `reserve(entity, area)`
2669:
2670:```typescript
2671:reserve(entity: EntityId, area: OccupancyArea): boolean
2672:```
2673:
2674:Creates or replaces a reservation for an entity. Returns `false` on conflict.
2675:
2676:#### `clearReservation(entity)`
2677:
2678:```typescript
2679:clearReservation(entity: EntityId): void
2680:```
2681:
2682:Clears only the reservation owned by the entity.
2683:
2684:#### `release(entity)`
2685:
2686:```typescript
2687:release(entity: EntityId): void
2688:```
2689:
2690:Clears both occupancy and reservation state for an entity.
2691:
2692:#### `getOccupant(x, y)`
2693:
2694:```typescript
2695:getOccupant(x: number, y: number): EntityId | null
2696:```
2697:
2698:Returns the entity occupying a cell, or `null`.
2699:
2700:#### `getReservationOwner(x, y)`
2701:
2702:```typescript
2703:getReservationOwner(x: number, y: number): EntityId | null
2704:```
2705:
2706:Returns the entity reserving a cell, or `null`.
2707:
2708:#### `getOccupiedCells(entity)`
2709:
2710:```typescript
2711:getOccupiedCells(entity: EntityId): Position[]
2712:```
2713:
2714:Returns the claimed occupied cells for an entity as positions.
2715:
2716:#### `getReservedCells(entity)`
2717:
2718:```typescript
2719:getReservedCells(entity: EntityId): Position[]
2720:```
2721:
2722:Returns the claimed reserved cells for an entity as positions.
2723:
2724:#### `getMetrics()`
2725:
2726:```typescript
2727:getMetrics(): OccupancyGridMetrics
2728:```
2729:
2730:Returns runtime scan counters for blocking checks, footprint claims, and snapshot reads.
2731:
2732:#### `resetMetrics()`
2733:
2734:```typescript
2735:resetMetrics(): void
2736:```
2737:
2738:Clears all accumulated `OccupancyGrid` counters without affecting occupancy state or `version`.
2739:
2740:#### `getState()`
2741:
2742:```typescript
2743:getState(): OccupancyGridState
