4186:
4187:## Render Adapter
4188:
4189:Projection boundary for renderer-facing snapshots and per-tick diffs. The engine stays headless; the game provides projection callbacks that decide what render state each entity exposes.
4190:
4191:```typescript
4192:import {
4193:  RenderAdapter,
4194:  type RenderDiff,
4195:  type RenderEntity,
4196:  type RenderProjector,
4197:  type RenderServerMessage,
4198:  type RenderSnapshot,
4199:} from 'civ-engine';
4200:```
4201:
4202:### Core Types
4203:
4204:#### `RenderEntity<TView>`
4205:
4206:```typescript
4207:interface RenderEntity<TView> {
4208:  ref: EntityRef;
4209:  view: TView;
4210:}
4211:```
4212:
4213:Projected renderable entity with a generation-aware entity reference.
4214:
4215:#### `RenderSnapshot<TView, TFrame>`
4216:
4217:```typescript
4218:interface RenderSnapshot<TView, TFrame> {
4219:  tick: number;
4220:  entities: Array<RenderEntity<TView>>;
4221:  frame: TFrame | null;
4222:}
4223:```
4224:
4225:Full projected render state for initial sync or resync.
4226:
4227:#### `RenderDiff<TView, TFrame>`
4228:
4229:```typescript
4230:interface RenderDiff<TView, TFrame> {
4231:  tick: number;
4232:  created: Array<RenderEntity<TView>>;
4233:  updated: Array<RenderEntity<TView>>;
4234:  destroyed: EntityRef[];
4235:  frame: TFrame | null;
4236:}
4237:```
4238:
4239:Incremental projected render update for one simulation tick.
4240:
4241:#### `RenderEntityChange`
4242:
4243:```typescript
4244:interface RenderEntityChange {
4245:  id: EntityId;
4246:  created: boolean;
4247:  destroyed: boolean;
4248:  componentKeys: string[];
4249:  resourceKeys: string[];
4250:  previousRef: EntityRef | null;
4251:  currentRef: EntityRef | null;
4252:}
4253:```
4254:
4255:Summary of why an entity was considered for re-projection on a tick.
4256:
4257:#### `RenderProjector<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TView, TFrame>`
4258:
4259:```typescript
4260:interface RenderProjector<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TView, TFrame> {
4261:  projectEntity(
4262:    ref: EntityRef,
4263:    world: World<TEventMap, TCommandMap>,
4264:    change: RenderEntityChange | null,
4265:  ): TView | null;
4266:  projectFrame?(
4267:    world: World<TEventMap, TCommandMap>,
4268:    diff: TickDiff | null,
4269:  ): TFrame | null;
4270:  shouldProjectChange?(change: RenderEntityChange): boolean;
4271:}
4272:```
4273:
4274:Game-owned callbacks that map simulation state to render-facing state.
4275:
4276:#### `RenderServerMessage<TView, TFrame, TDebug>`
4277:
4278:```typescript
4279:type RenderServerMessage<TView, TFrame, TDebug> =
4280:  | { type: 'renderSnapshot'; data: { render: RenderSnapshot<TView, TFrame>; debug: TDebug | null } }
4281:  | { type: 'renderTick'; data: { render: RenderDiff<TView, TFrame>; debug: TDebug | null } };
4282:```
4283:
4284:Message union emitted by `RenderAdapter`.
4285:
4286:### Constructor
4287:
4288:```typescript
4289:new RenderAdapter<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TView, TFrame, TDebug>(config: {
4290:  world: World<TEventMap, TCommandMap>;
4291:  projector: RenderProjector<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TView, TFrame>;
4292:  send: (message: RenderServerMessage<TView, TFrame, TDebug>) => void;
4293:  onError?: (error: unknown) => void;
4294:  debug?: { capture(): TDebug | null };
4295:})
4296:```
4297:
4298:### Methods
4299:
4300:#### `connect()`
4301:
4302:```typescript
4303:connect(): void
4304:```
4305:
4306:Immediately sends a `renderSnapshot` message, then subscribes to world diffs and emits `renderTick` messages after each step.
4307:
4308:#### `disconnect()`
4309:
4310:```typescript
4311:disconnect(): void
4312:```
4313:
4314:Stops streaming render messages.
4315:
4316:### Behavior Notes
4317:
4318:- Render messages use `EntityRef` values so same-tick ID recycling is unambiguous.
4319:- `projectEntity()` returning `null` removes an entity from the render surface without destroying it in the simulation.
4320:- `debug.capture()` is optional and can attach structured debugger output to each render message.
4321:
