4323:
4324:## Scenario Runner
4325:
4326:Headless setup/run/check harness for deterministic experiments. Intended for AI agents, integration tests, and debug workflows that need one structured result object instead of ad hoc setup code.
4327:
4328:```typescript
4329:import {
4330:  runScenario,
4331:  type ScenarioCapture,
4332:  type ScenarioCheck,
4333:  type ScenarioContext,
4334:  type ScenarioFailure,
4335:  type ScenarioResult,
4336:  type ScenarioStepUntilResult,
4337:} from 'civ-engine';
4338:```
4339:
4340:### Core Types
4341:
4342:#### `ScenarioFailure`
4343:
4344:```typescript
4345:interface ScenarioFailure {
4346:  code: string;
4347:  message: string;
4348:  source?: 'setup' | 'run' | 'stepUntil' | 'check' | 'tick';
4349:  details?: JsonValue;
4350:}
4351:```
4352:
4353:Structured failure object used by runner-level failures, `stepUntil()`, and checks.
4354:
4355:#### `ScenarioCheck`
4356:
4357:```typescript
4358:interface ScenarioCheck<TEventMap, TCommandMap> {
4359:  name: string;
4360:  check(
4361:    context: ScenarioContext<TEventMap, TCommandMap>,
4362:  ): boolean | ScenarioFailure;
4363:}
4364:```
4365:
4366:Post-run check evaluated after `run()`.
4367:
4368:#### `ScenarioContext`
4369:
4370:```typescript
4371:interface ScenarioContext<TEventMap, TCommandMap> {
4372:  name: string;
4373:  world: World<TEventMap, TCommandMap>;
4374:  debugger: WorldDebugger<TEventMap, TCommandMap>;
4375:  history: WorldHistoryRecorder<TEventMap, TCommandMap, WorldDebugSnapshot>;
4376:  submit<K extends keyof TCommandMap>(
4377:    type: K,
4378:    data: TCommandMap[K],
4379:  ): CommandSubmissionResult<K>;
4380:  step(count?: number): ScenarioCapture<TEventMap, TCommandMap>;
4381:  stepUntil(
4382:    predicate: (context: ScenarioContext<TEventMap, TCommandMap>) => boolean,
4383:    options?: {
4384:      maxTicks?: number;
4385:      code?: string;
4386:      message?: string;
4387:      details?: JsonValue;
4388:    },
4389:  ): ScenarioStepUntilResult;
4390:  capture(): ScenarioCapture<TEventMap, TCommandMap>;
4391:  fail(
4392:    code: string,
4393:    message: string,
4394:    details?: JsonValue,
4395:    source?: ScenarioFailure['source'],
4396:  ): ScenarioFailure;
4397:}
4398:```
4399:
4400:Runtime helpers exposed to `setup()`, `run()`, and checks.
4401:
4402:#### `ScenarioStepUntilResult`
4403:
4404:```typescript
4405:interface ScenarioStepUntilResult {
4406:  completed: boolean;
4407:  steps: number;
4408:  tick: number;
4409:  failure: ScenarioFailure | null;
4410:}
4411:```
4412:
4413:Bounded loop result returned by `context.stepUntil()`.
4414:
4415:#### `ScenarioResult`
4416:
4417:```typescript
4418:interface ScenarioResult<TEventMap, TCommandMap>
4419:  extends ScenarioCapture<TEventMap, TCommandMap> {
4420:  name: string;
4421:  passed: boolean;
4422:  failure: ScenarioFailure | null;
4423:  checks: ScenarioCheckOutcome[];
4424:  issues: DebugIssue[];
4425:}
4426:```
4427:
4428:Final machine-readable result from `runScenario()`.
4429:`ScenarioCapture` and `ScenarioResult` include `schemaVersion`.
4430:
4431:### `runScenario(config)`
4432:
4433:```typescript
4434:runScenario<TEventMap, TCommandMap>(config: {
4435:  name: string;
4436:  world: World<TEventMap, TCommandMap>;
4437:  debugger?: WorldDebugger<TEventMap, TCommandMap>;
4438:  probes?: DebugProbe[];
4439:  history?: {
4440:    capacity?: number;
4441:    commandCapacity?: number;
4442:    captureInitialSnapshot?: boolean;
4443:  };
4444:  setup?(context: ScenarioContext<TEventMap, TCommandMap>): void;
4445:  run?(
4446:    context: ScenarioContext<TEventMap, TCommandMap>,
4447:  ): void | ScenarioFailure | null;
4448:  checks?: Array<ScenarioCheck<TEventMap, TCommandMap>>;
4449:}): ScenarioResult<TEventMap, TCommandMap>
4450:```
4451:
4452:Runs a scenario and returns the final structured result.
4453:
4454:### Behavior Notes
4455:
4456:- The runner creates a `WorldHistoryRecorder` and clears it after `setup()`, so the recorded initial snapshot reflects the prepared scenario state.
4457:- `submit()` inside the scenario context calls `world.submitWithResult()`.
4458:- `step()` inside the scenario context uses `world.stepWithResult()`, so runtime tick failures are converted into structured scenario failures.
4459:- `stepUntil()` returns a structured timeout failure instead of forcing the caller to throw.
4460:- Exceptions thrown by `setup()`, `run()`, or checks are converted into structured runner failures when possible.
4461:
