4650:
4651:## Session Recording — Bundle Types & Errors
4652:
4653:The session-recording subsystem captures deterministic, replayable bundles of `World` runs. This section documents the bundle / marker / error type definitions; subsequent sections cover the sink interfaces, recorder, replayer, and scenario adapter.
4654:
4655:See `docs/guides/session-recording.md` for the user-facing guide and `docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md` for the full subsystem design.
4656:
4657:### `SessionBundle`
4658:
4659:```typescript
4660:const SESSION_BUNDLE_SCHEMA_VERSION = 1;
4661:
4662:interface SessionBundle<
4663:  TEventMap = Record<string, never>,
4664:  TCommandMap = Record<string, never>,
4665:  TDebug = JsonValue,
4666:> {
4667:  schemaVersion: typeof SESSION_BUNDLE_SCHEMA_VERSION;
4668:  metadata: SessionMetadata;
4669:  initialSnapshot: WorldSnapshot;
4670:  ticks: SessionTickEntry<TEventMap, TDebug>[];
4671:  commands: RecordedCommand<TCommandMap>[];
4672:  executions: CommandExecutionResult<keyof TCommandMap>[];
4673:  failures: TickFailure[];
4674:  snapshots: SessionSnapshotEntry[];
4675:  markers: Marker[];
4676:  attachments: AttachmentDescriptor[];
4677:}
4678:```
4679:
4680:Strict JSON: `JSON.stringify(bundle)` is a complete, lossless representation of everything in the JSON shape (sidecar attachment bytes are stored externally; consumers retrieve them via `source.readSidecar(id)` once T2 lands).
4681:
4682:### `SessionMetadata`
4683:
4684:```typescript
4685:interface SessionMetadata {
4686:  sessionId: string;          // UUID v4
4687:  engineVersion: string;      // ENGINE_VERSION at recording time
4688:  nodeVersion: string;        // process.version at recording time
4689:  recordedAt: string;         // ISO 8601 timestamp
4690:  startTick: number;          // tick at connect()
4691:  endTick: number;            // tick at disconnect() (live world.tick)
4692:  persistedEndTick: number;   // tick of last successfully persisted snapshot
4693:  durationTicks: number;      // endTick - startTick
4694:  sourceKind: 'session' | 'scenario';
4695:  sourceLabel?: string;
4696:  incomplete?: true;          // set when recorder did not reach disconnect cleanly
4697:  failedTicks?: number[];     // ticks at-or-after which replay refuses (TickFailure spans)
4698:}
4699:```
4700:
4701:`endTick` is the live world tick at finalization regardless of persistence success; `persistedEndTick` is the upper bound for incomplete-bundle replay (per spec §5.2 manifest cadence).
4702:
4703:### `Marker`
4704:
4705:```typescript
4706:type MarkerKind = 'annotation' | 'assertion' | 'checkpoint';
4707:type MarkerProvenance = 'engine' | 'game';
4708:
4709:interface EntityRef { id: number; generation: number; }
4710:
4711:interface MarkerRefs {
4712:  entities?: EntityRef[];                           // matched by id + generation
4713:  cells?: Position[];                               // must be in-bounds
4714:  tickRange?: { from: number; to: number };
4715:}
4716:
4717:interface Marker {
4718:  id: string;                  // UUID v4
4719:  tick: number;                // engine tick the marker references; >= 0
4720:  kind: MarkerKind;
4721:  provenance: MarkerProvenance;
4722:  text?: string;
4723:  refs?: MarkerRefs;
4724:  data?: JsonValue;            // opaque game payload
4725:  attachments?: string[];      // attachment ids
4726:  createdAt?: string;          // ISO 8601 (recorder fills in if omitted)
4727:  validated?: false;           // retroactive markers; entity-liveness skipped
4728:}
4729:```
4730:
4731:`MarkerProvenance.engine` is reserved for `scenarioResultToBundle()`; recorder-added markers always get `provenance: 'game'`.
4732:
4733:### `RecordedCommand`
4734:
4735:```typescript
4736:interface RecordedCommand<TCommandMap = Record<string, unknown>> {
4737:  submissionTick: number;     // CommandSubmissionResult.tick (observable tick at submit)
4738:  sequence: number;           // CommandSubmissionResult.sequence; orders within a tick
4739:  type: keyof TCommandMap & string;
4740:  data: TCommandMap[keyof TCommandMap];
4741:  result: CommandSubmissionResult<keyof TCommandMap>;
4742:}
4743:```
4744:
4745:Replay-ready: carries the original `data` payload that `CommandSubmissionResult` alone does not.
4746:
4747:### `AttachmentDescriptor`
4748:
4749:```typescript
4750:interface AttachmentDescriptor {
4751:  id: string;                 // UUID v4
4752:  mime: string;
4753:  sizeBytes: number;
4754:  ref: { dataUrl: string } | { sidecar: true };
4755:}
4756:```
4757:
4758:Two ref shapes: `{ dataUrl }` embeds bytes as `data:<mime>;base64,...` directly in the bundle JSON; `{ sidecar: true }` stores bytes externally (FileSink: `attachments/<id>.<ext>`; MemorySink: parallel internal map accessed via `source.readSidecar(id)`).
4759:
4760:### Error Hierarchy
4761:
4762:```typescript
4763:class SessionRecordingError extends Error {
4764:  readonly details: JsonValue | undefined;
4765:  constructor(message: string, details?: JsonValue);
4766:}
4767:
4768:class MarkerValidationError extends SessionRecordingError {
4769:  readonly referencesValidationRule: string | undefined;
4770:  constructor(message: string, details?: JsonValue, referencesValidationRule?: string);
4771:}
4772:
4773:class RecorderClosedError extends SessionRecordingError;     // post-disconnect, poisoned-world, recorder_already_attached
4774:class SinkWriteError extends SessionRecordingError;          // I/O failure during recording
4775:class BundleVersionError extends SessionRecordingError;      // schemaVersion / engineVersion incompat
4776:class BundleRangeError extends SessionRecordingError;        // openAt / tickEntriesBetween out-of-range
4777:class BundleIntegrityError extends SessionRecordingError;    // structural; replay_across_failure / no_replay_payloads / no_initial_snapshot
4778:class ReplayHandlerMissingError extends SessionRecordingError;  // worldFactory drift on a recorded command type
4779:```
4780:
4781:Catch sites that care about cause use `instanceof <Subclass>`; catch sites that just want "any session-recording problem" use `instanceof SessionRecordingError`.
4782:
4783:### `ENGINE_VERSION`
4784:
4785:```typescript
4786:const ENGINE_VERSION: string;  // matches package.json's `version` field
4787:```
4788:
4789:Read by `SessionRecorder` and `scenarioResultToBundle()` for `metadata.engineVersion`. Kept in sync with `package.json`'s `version` by the release process.
4790:
4791:## Session Recording — Sinks (SessionSink, SessionSource, MemorySink)
4792:
4793:`SessionSink` (write) / `SessionSource` (read) interfaces plus `MemorySink` reference implementation. Bundle types travel through these.
4794:
4795:### `SessionSink`
4796:
4797:```typescript
4798:interface SessionSink {
4799:  open(metadata: SessionMetadata): void;
4800:  writeTick(entry: SessionTickEntry): void;
4801:  writeCommand(record: RecordedCommand): void;
4802:  writeCommandExecution(result: CommandExecutionResult): void;
4803:  writeTickFailure(failure: TickFailure): void;
4804:  writeSnapshot(entry: SessionSnapshotEntry): void;
4805:  writeMarker(marker: Marker): void;
4806:  writeAttachment(descriptor: AttachmentDescriptor, data: Uint8Array): AttachmentDescriptor;
4807:  close(): void;
4808:}
4809:```
4810:
4811:All methods are synchronous (per spec §8 — composes with `World.onDiff`'s synchronous listener invariants). `writeAttachment` returns the finalized descriptor (sinks may rewrite `ref` from `{ dataUrl: '<placeholder>' }` to a populated data URL, or downgrade to sidecar).
4812:
4813:### `SessionSource`
4814:
4815:```typescript
4816:interface SessionSource {
4817:  readonly metadata: SessionMetadata;
4818:  readSnapshot(tick: number): WorldSnapshot;
4819:  readSidecar(id: string): Uint8Array;
4820:  ticks(): IterableIterator<SessionTickEntry>;
4821:  commands(): IterableIterator<RecordedCommand>;
4822:  executions(): IterableIterator<CommandExecutionResult>;
4823:  failures(): IterableIterator<TickFailure>;
4824:  markers(): IterableIterator<Marker>;
4825:  attachments(): IterableIterator<AttachmentDescriptor>;
4826:  toBundle(): SessionBundle;
4827:}
4828:```
4829:
4830:Read interface paired with `SessionSink`. `MemorySink` and `FileSink` both implement the union (`SessionSink & SessionSource`).
4831:
4832:### `MemorySink`
4833:
4834:```typescript
4835:new MemorySink(options?: MemorySinkOptions);
4836:
4837:interface MemorySinkOptions {
4838:  allowSidecar?: boolean;          // default false; oversize attachments throw without it
4839:  sidecarThresholdBytes?: number;  // default 65536 (64 KiB)
4840:}
4841:```
4842:
4843:Holds writes in in-memory arrays. Sidecar attachment bytes go in a parallel internal `Map<string, Uint8Array>` accessed via `readSidecar(id)`.
4844:
4845:Defaults: attachments under the threshold embed as `data:<mime>;base64,...` URLs in the manifest. Attachments over the threshold throw `SinkWriteError(code: 'oversize_attachment')` UNLESS `allowSidecar: true` is set, in which case they're stored as sidecars. Callers can also force sidecar storage explicitly by passing `ref: { sidecar: true }` to `writeAttachment`.
4846:
4847:`toBundle()` returns the canonical strict-JSON `SessionBundle`. The first written snapshot becomes `bundle.initialSnapshot`; subsequent snapshots populate `bundle.snapshots[]`. Throws `SinkWriteError(code: 'no_snapshots')` if no snapshots have been written.
4848:
4849:## Session Recording — FileSink
4850:
4851:Disk-backed `SessionSink & SessionSource`.
4852:
4853:### `FileSink`
4854:
4855:```typescript
4856:new FileSink(bundleDir: string);
4857:```
4858:
4859:On-disk layout:
4860:
4861:```
4862:<bundleDir>/
4863:  manifest.json            // SessionMetadata + dataUrl attachments + sidecar refs
4864:  ticks.jsonl              // append-only; one SessionTickEntry per line
4865:  commands.jsonl           // append-only; one RecordedCommand per line
4866:  executions.jsonl         // append-only; one CommandExecutionResult per line
4867:  failures.jsonl           // append-only; one TickFailure per line
4868:  markers.jsonl            // append-only; one Marker per line
4869:  snapshots/<tick>.json    // one snapshot per file
4870:  attachments/<id>.<ext>   // sidecar bytes (extension from MIME table)
4871:```
4872:
4873:Manifest is rewritten on `open()`, on each `writeSnapshot()` (advancing `metadata.persistedEndTick`), and on `close()` — atomic via `.tmp.json` → `.json` rename. Per-tick rewrites are NOT performed.
4874:
4875:**Default attachment policy: sidecar.** FileSink is disk-backed; the disk-storage path is the natural default. Pass `descriptor.ref: { dataUrl: '<placeholder>' }` to opt into manifest embedding (only useful for very small blobs).
4876:
4877:**MIME → file extension table:** `image/png` → `.png`, `image/jpeg` → `.jpg`, `image/gif` → `.gif`, `image/webp` → `.webp`, `image/svg+xml` → `.svg`, `application/json` → `.json`, `application/octet-stream` → `.bin`, `text/plain` → `.txt`, `text/csv` → `.csv`. Unknown MIMEs fall back to `.bin`. The manifest carries the full MIME so readers can recover the original.
4878:
4879:`SessionSource` methods:
4880:- `readSnapshot(tick)`: reads from `snapshots/<tick>.json`. Throws if missing.
4881:- `readSidecar(id)`: reads from `attachments/<id>.<ext>`. Throws if the descriptor is `dataUrl`-mode rather than sidecar.
4882:- `ticks()`, `commands()`, `executions()`, `failures()`, `markers()`: lazy generators streaming the JSONL files. Tolerate a trailing partial line (e.g. a crash mid-write).
4883:- `toBundle()`: reads all snapshot files, sorts numerically, returns a `SessionBundle` whose `initialSnapshot` is the lowest-tick snapshot.
4884:
4885:## Session Recording — SessionRecorder
4886:
4887:```typescript
4888:class SessionRecorder<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TDebug = JsonValue> {
4889:  constructor(config: SessionRecorderConfig<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TDebug>);
4890:  readonly sessionId: string;
4891:  readonly tickCount: number;
4892:  readonly markerCount: number;
4893:  readonly snapshotCount: number;
4894:  readonly isConnected: boolean;
4895:  readonly isClosed: boolean;
4896:  readonly lastError: SessionRecordingError | null;
4897:  connect(): void;
4898:  disconnect(): void;
4899:  addMarker(marker: NewMarker): string;
4900:  attach(blob: { mime: string; data: Uint8Array }, options?: { sidecar?: boolean }): string;
4901:  takeSnapshot(): SessionSnapshotEntry;
4902:  toBundle(): SessionBundle<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TDebug>;
4903:}
4904:
4905:interface SessionRecorderConfig {
4906:  world: World;
4907:  sink?: SessionSink & SessionSource;       // default: new MemorySink()
4908:  snapshotInterval?: number | null;          // default: 1000; null disables periodic
4909:  terminalSnapshot?: boolean;                // default: true
4910:  debug?: { capture(): TDebug | null };
4911:  sourceLabel?: string;
4912:}
4913:
4914:type NewMarker = Omit<Marker, 'id' | 'createdAt' | 'provenance' | 'tick'> & { tick?: number };
4915:```
4916:
4917:`connect()` rejects: poisoned world (`code: 'world_poisoned'`); already-attached payload-capturing recorder (`code: 'recorder_already_attached'`); post-disconnect (`code: 'already_closed'`).
4918:
4919:`addMarker(input)` validates per spec §6.1: live-tick `EntityRef`s match via `world.isCurrent`; cells in-bounds; tickRange well-formed; attachment ids registered via `attach()` first. Retroactive markers (tick < world.tick) skip entity liveness and are stamped `validated: false`. All recorder-added markers get `provenance: 'game'`.
4920:
4921:`attach(blob, options)` defaults to "no preference; each sink applies its own default policy" — `MemorySink` routes under-threshold attachments to `dataUrl` and oversize to sidecar (with `allowSidecar`); `FileSink` keeps every blob as a sidecar file. Pass `options.sidecar: true` to force sidecar regardless of sink, or `options.sidecar: false` to force `dataUrl` embedding.
4922:
4923:## Session Recording — SessionReplayer
4924:
4925:```typescript
4926:class SessionReplayer<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TDebug> {
4927:  static fromBundle(bundle: SessionBundle, config: ReplayerConfig): SessionReplayer;
4928:  static fromSource(source: SessionSource, config: ReplayerConfig): SessionReplayer;
4929:  readonly metadata: SessionMetadata;
4930:  readonly markerCount: number;
4931:  markers(): Marker[];
4932:  markersAt(tick: number): Marker[];
4933:  markersOfKind(kind: MarkerKind): Marker[];
4934:  markersByEntity(ref: EntityRef): Marker[];   // exact id+generation match
4935:  markersByEntityId(id: number): Marker[];     // any generation
4936:  snapshotTicks(): number[];
4937:  ticks(): number[];
4938:  openAt(tick: number): World;
4939:  stateAtTick(tick: number): WorldSnapshot;
4940:  tickEntriesBetween(fromTick: number, toTick: number): SessionTickEntry[];  // inclusive both ends
4941:  selfCheck(options?: SelfCheckOptions): SelfCheckResult;
4942:  validateMarkers(): MarkerValidationResult;
4943:}
4944:
4945:interface ReplayerConfig {
4946:  worldFactory: (snapshot: WorldSnapshot) => World;  // part of determinism contract per ADR 4
4947:}
4948:
4949:interface SelfCheckOptions {
4950:  stopOnFirstDivergence?: boolean;   // default false
4951:  checkState?: boolean;              // default true
4952:  checkEvents?: boolean;             // default true
4953:  checkExecutions?: boolean;         // default true
4954:}
4955:
4956:interface SelfCheckResult {
4957:  ok: boolean;
4958:  checkedSegments: number;
4959:  stateDivergences: StateDivergence[];
4960:  eventDivergences: EventDivergence[];
4961:  executionDivergences: ExecutionDivergence[];
4962:  skippedSegments: SkippedSegment[];      // segments containing failedTicks
4963:}
4964:
4965:function deepEqualWithPath(a: unknown, b: unknown, path?: string): { equal: boolean; firstDifferingPath?: string };
4966:```
4967:
4968:Range checks per spec §9.1: `< startTick` or `> endTick` (or `> persistedEndTick` for incomplete bundles) throws `BundleRangeError`. `tick` at-or-after first `failedTicks` throws `BundleIntegrityError(code: 'replay_across_failure')`. Replay forward without payloads throws `BundleIntegrityError(code: 'no_replay_payloads')`. Missing handler in factory throws `ReplayHandlerMissingError`. Engine version cross-`b` throws `BundleVersionError`; within-`b` warns. Cross-Node-major warns.
4969:
4970:`selfCheck` walks consecutive snapshot pairs (initial + periodic + terminal). 3-stream comparison: state via `deepEqualWithPath`, events ordered structural equality, executions ordered structural equality (excluding `submissionSequence` which resets per segment until snapshot v6 lands). Failure spans skipped.
4971:
4972:## Session Recording — scenarioResultToBundle
4973:
4974:```typescript
4975:function scenarioResultToBundle(
4976:  result: ScenarioResult,
4977:  options?: ScenarioResultToBundleOptions,
4978:): SessionBundle;
4979:
4980:interface ScenarioResultToBundleOptions {
4981:  sourceLabel?: string;       // default: result.name
4982:  nodeVersion?: string;        // default: process.version
4983:}
4984:```
4985:
4986:Translates `runScenario` output to a `SessionBundle` with `sourceKind: 'scenario'`. One `kind: 'assertion'` marker per `result.checks` outcome with `provenance: 'engine'`. `metadata.startTick` from `result.history.initialSnapshot.tick` (NOT hardcoded 0). Throws `BundleIntegrityError(code: 'no_initial_snapshot')` when scenario was configured with `captureInitialSnapshot: false`. Replayable bundle requires `runScenario({ history: { captureCommandPayloads: true } })`; otherwise `bundle.commands` is empty and replay refuses with `BundleIntegrityError(code: 'no_replay_payloads')`.
4987:
4988:## Synthetic Playtest — Policies (v0.7.20)
4989:
4990:The synthetic playtest harness drives a `World` via pluggable `Policy` functions for `N` ticks, producing a `SessionBundle` for AI-first feedback loops (Tier 1 of `docs/design/ai-first-dev-roadmap.md`). T1 ships the policy types and three built-in factories. The end-to-end harness `runSynthPlaytest` ships in v0.8.0 (T2).
4991:
4992:```typescript
4993:import type { World, ComponentRegistry } from 'civ-engine';
4994:
4995:interface PolicyContext<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TComponents = Record<string, unknown>, TState = Record<string, unknown>> {
4996:  readonly world: World<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TComponents, TState>;
4997:  readonly tick: number;       // The tick about to execute (commands submitted now run during this tick).
4998:  readonly random: () => number;  // Seeded sub-RNG independent of world.rng. Use this, NOT world.random().
4999:}
5000:
5001:interface StopContext<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TComponents, TState> {
5002:  readonly world: World<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TComponents, TState>;
5003:  readonly tick: number;       // The tick that just executed (post-step world.tick).
5004:  readonly random: () => number;
5005:}
5006:
5007:type PolicyCommand<TCommandMap> = {
5008:  [K in keyof TCommandMap & string]: { type: K; data: TCommandMap[K] };
5009:}[keyof TCommandMap & string];
5010:
5011:type Policy<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TComponents, TState> = (
5012:  context: PolicyContext<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TComponents, TState>,
5013:) => PolicyCommand<TCommandMap>[];
5014:```
5015:
5016:**Determinism contract:** Policies are external coordinators per spec §11.1 clause 2. They MUST be deterministic given their inputs (`world` state, `tick`, `random()`). Any randomness MUST flow through `ctx.random()` — `Math.random()`, `world.random()`, `Date.now()`, `process.env`, and other non-deterministic sources are forbidden. Policies MUST NOT mutate the world directly; mutation goes through the returned `PolicyCommand[]` which the harness submits via `world.submitWithResult`. `SessionReplayer.selfCheck` is the verification mechanism for non-poisoned bundles.
5017:
5018:### `noopPolicy()`
5019:
5020:```typescript
5021:function noopPolicy<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TComponents, TState>(): Policy<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TComponents, TState>;
5022:```
5023:
5024:Submits nothing. Useful for letting world systems advance without external input.
5025:
5026:### `randomPolicy(config)`
5027:
5028:```typescript
5029:interface RandomPolicyConfig<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TComponents, TState> {
5030:  catalog: Array<(ctx: PolicyContext<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TComponents, TState>) => PolicyCommand<TCommandMap>>;
5031:  frequency?: number;  // default 1
5032:  offset?: number;     // default 0; must be < frequency
5033:  burst?: number;      // default 1
5034:}
5035:
5036:function randomPolicy<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TComponents, TState>(
5037:  config: RandomPolicyConfig<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TComponents, TState>,
5038:): Policy<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TComponents, TState>;
5039:```
5040:
5041:Picks a random catalog entry per emit via `ctx.random()`. Emits on ticks where `tick % frequency === offset`. `burst` controls commands per fired tick. Catalog functions receive `PolicyContext` so they can reference live world state. Throws `RangeError` for empty catalog, non-positive-integer frequency/burst, or out-of-range offset.
5042:
5043:### `scriptedPolicy(sequence)`
5044:
5045:```typescript
5046:type ScriptedPolicyEntry<TCommandMap> = {
5047:  [K in keyof TCommandMap & string]: { tick: number; type: K; data: TCommandMap[K] };
5048:}[keyof TCommandMap & string];
5049:
5050:function scriptedPolicy<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TComponents, TState>(
5051:  sequence: ScriptedPolicyEntry<TCommandMap>[],
5052:): Policy<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TComponents, TState>;
5053:```
5054:
5055:Plays back a pre-recorded list of `{ tick, type, data }` entries. Pre-grouped by tick at construction (O(1) per-tick lookup). Ticks not in the sequence emit nothing. `entry.tick` is matched against `PolicyContext.tick` (the tick about to execute), NOT `world.tick` at submit time. **Bundle → script conversion** (e.g., for regression playback of a recorded bug): bundle `RecordedCommand.submissionTick` is one less than the executing tick, so:
5056:
5057:```typescript
5058:const sequence = bundle.commands.map((cmd) => ({
5059:  tick: cmd.submissionTick + 1,
5060:  type: cmd.type,
5061:  data: cmd.data,
5062:}));
5063:```
5064:
5065:## Synthetic Playtest — Harness (v0.8.0)
5066:
5067:`runSynthPlaytest` drives a `World` via pluggable policies for `N` ticks and produces a `SessionBundle`. T2 of Spec 3.
5068:
5069:### `runSynthPlaytest(config)`
5070:
5071:```typescript
5072:function runSynthPlaytest<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TComponents, TState, TDebug = JsonValue>(
5073:  config: SynthPlaytestConfig<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TComponents, TState>,
5074:): SynthPlaytestResult<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TDebug>;
5075:```
5076:
5077:Lifecycle (per spec v10 §7.1):
5078:1. **Validate** `maxTicks >= 1`, `policySeed` is finite integer.
5079:2. **Init sub-RNG** from `policySeed` (default: `Math.floor(world.random() * 0x1_0000_0000)`). Happens BEFORE `recorder.connect()` so the initial snapshot captures post-derivation `world.rng` state.
5080:3. **Attach** `SessionRecorder` with `sourceKind: 'synthetic'` and `terminalSnapshot: true` hardcoded. If `recorder.lastError` is set after `connect()` (sink open failure), re-throw — no coherent bundle to return.
5081:4. **Tick loop**: per tick, build `policyCtx`, call each policy in array order, submit returned commands via `world.submitWithResult`, call `world.step()`, check `recorder.lastError`, increment `ticksRun`, evaluate `stopWhen` with a fresh `StopContext`. Stop conditions: `maxTicks`, `stopWhen`, `poisoned`, `policyError`, `sinkError` (mid-tick).
5082:5. **Disconnect** + return `{ bundle, ticksRun, stopReason, ok, policyError? }`.
5083:
5084:`ok` is `true` for `'maxTicks' | 'stopWhen' | 'poisoned' | 'policyError'` (bundle is valid up to the failure point); `false` for `'sinkError'`.
5085:
5086:### `SynthPlaytestConfig`
5087:
5088:```typescript
5089:interface SynthPlaytestConfig<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TComponents, TState> {
5090:  world: World<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TComponents, TState>;
5091:  policies: Policy<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TComponents, TState>[];
5092:  maxTicks: number;                    // required, >= 1
5093:  sink?: SessionSink & SessionSource;  // default: new MemorySink()
5094:  sourceLabel?: string;                 // default: 'synthetic'
5095:  policySeed?: number;                  // default: derived from world.random() at construction
5096:  stopWhen?: (ctx: StopContext<...>) => boolean;
5097:  snapshotInterval?: number | null;    // default 1000; null disables periodic snapshots
5098:}
5099:```
5100:
5101:`terminalSnapshot` is intentionally NOT exposed — the harness always passes `terminalSnapshot: true` to `SessionRecorder` so every bundle has the `(initial, terminal)` segment for `selfCheck`.
5102:
5103:### `SynthPlaytestResult`
5104:
5105:```typescript
5106:interface SynthPlaytestResult<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TDebug = JsonValue> {
5107:  bundle: SessionBundle<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TDebug>;
5108:  ticksRun: number;
5109:  stopReason: 'maxTicks' | 'stopWhen' | 'poisoned' | 'policyError' | 'sinkError';
5110:  ok: boolean;
5111:  policyError?: { policyIndex: number; tick: number; error: { name; message; stack } };
5112:}
5113:```
5114:
5115:`ticksRun` = count of `world.step()` invocations that completed AND were followed by a clean `recorder.lastError` check. With `K = world.tick - startTick`:
5116:
5117:| stopReason | ticksRun |
5118:|---|---|
5119:| `'maxTicks'`, `'stopWhen'`, `'policyError'` | `K` |
5120:| `'poisoned'`, `'sinkError'` (mid-tick) | `K - 1` |
5121:
5122:`policyError` is populated only when `stopReason === 'policyError'`. `bundle.failures` is NOT modified for policy throws — `failedTicks` is reserved for world-level tick failures.
5123:
5124:### Determinism — CI guard pattern
5125:
5126:`SessionReplayer.selfCheck()` is meaningful for non-poisoned synthetic bundles where `ticksRun >= 1`. For `stopReason === 'poisoned'` bundles, `selfCheck()` re-throws the original tick failure (the failed-tick-bounded final segment is replayed). For `ticksRun === 0`, the terminal snapshot equals the initial → `selfCheck()` returns `ok:true` vacuously.
5127:
5128:```typescript
5129:if (result.ok && result.stopReason !== 'poisoned' && result.ticksRun >= 1) {
5130:  expect(replayer.selfCheck().ok).toBe(true);
5131:}
5132:```
5133:
5134:### Updated existing surface
5135:
5136:- `SessionMetadata.sourceKind` widened to `'session' | 'scenario' | 'synthetic'`. **Breaking** for downstream `assertNever` exhaustive switches (b-bump in 0.8.0).
5137:- `SessionMetadata.policySeed?: number` added. Populated when `sourceKind === 'synthetic'`.
5138:- `SessionRecorderConfig.sourceKind?: 'session' | 'scenario' | 'synthetic'` added (default `'session'`).
5139:- `SessionRecorderConfig.policySeed?: number` added.
